cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the mechanism and improvement of adaptive stochastic optimization algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also includes extensive experimental results on image classification (cs.CV), language modeling (cs.CL), and neural machine translation (cs.AI), indicating that these sub-categories are also relevant. Additionally, the paper proposes a new variant of Adam, which is a popular optimization algorithm in neural networks, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
